# Test RPM Package

File: test-package.rpm
Size: ~11KB
Original: rootfiles-8.1-31.el9.noarch.rpm from CentOS Stream 9

This is a small, real RPM package used for testing the gpg shim with actual
rpmsign commands. It was downloaded from:
https://mirror.stream.centos.org/9-stream/BaseOS/x86_64/os/Packages/

The rootfiles package is a minimal base package that contains basic /root
directory files. It's perfect for testing because:
- Very small size (11KB)
- Real, valid RPM format
- No dependencies
- Publicly available from CentOS mirrors

To test signing:
  make test-rpm

Or manually:
  export GNUPGHOME=$(pwd)/.gnupg
  export GPG_SIGNING_SERVER=http://localhost:8080/sign
  cp test-package.rpm test-signed.rpm
  rpmsign --define "_gpg_path $(pwd)/gpgshim" --addsign test-signed.rpm
